node.text:
To celebrate @elijahcraig Old-Fashioned Week, Lynnette Marrero (@drinksat6), bar director of Llama San (@llamasannyc), Llama Inn (@llamainnnyc) and Wonderbar (@wonderbarbeacon), shares how to make her Three Bites of the Apple, an Old-Fashioned inspired by autumn in the Hudson Valley. ⁠
Get the recipe at punchdrink.com and learn more about how you can raise an Elijah Craig Bourbon Old-Fashioned to support the bar community at OldFashionedWeek.com.
#punchpartner @elijahcraig #oldfashionedweek @rwcfusa 
#oldfashioned #cocktail #bartender

Welcome to a special charity episode of “Tip Your Bartender” all about Aperitivo to benefit @rwcfusa! This episode supports industry workers in need by raising funds for @rwcfusa. You can make a contribution by going to the link in our profile, or heading over to @rwcfusa. To date, the Bacardi family of brands has contributed over $150,000 to aid in @rwcfusa’s ongoing relief efforts. @martinirossius will continue their support with a donation following this segment. #raiseyourspirits #drinkpunchtyb

node.text: Seeking an upgrade to your summer spritz? You can't go wrong with @steakbonestacey’s watermelon Negroni Sbagliato variation. In the Tan Line Spritz, she swaps Campari for Cappelleti, sweet vermouth for dry and then mixes it with watermelon juice and prosecco for a cocktail that's light, bright and universally appealing. Head to the link in our profile for the recipe. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text:
Some would say there’s no more quintessential bar order than the Old-Fashioned. That’s why we’re welcoming the return of Elijah Craig Bourbon’s (@elijahcraig #punchpartner) annual Old-Fashioned Week, October 15–24, 2021. This celebration features a mix of events designed to bring people together to enjoy this classic bourbon cocktail. Old-Fashioned Week will also raise funds to support the Restaurant Workers’ Community Foundation, an advocacy and action nonprofit created by and for hospitality workers. Head to the link in our profile to learn more and get your bar or restaurant involved.⁠
📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Inspired by the daiquiri Hemingway famously drank at El Floridita, @bobby_heugel and @tommyho832 Floritida Daiquiri Frappé is their frozen take on the Papa Doble. Paying tribute to the Cuban original, the drink follows the classic recipe with dry white rum, maraschino liqueur, lime and granulated sugar, all blended with crushed ice and garnished with a lime wheel. Get their frosty update via the link in our profile. 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 01, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: There's a growing number of distillers who are looking beyond the confines of spirit categories in search of something more postmodern—and elusive. This breed, of which @empiricalcph was arguably the pioneer, makes distillates that do not fall into any of the traditional—and typically rigorously, legally defined—categories like gin, whiskey or vodka. Instead, they distill whatever they want, however they want, peppers to pineapple. And they seem to have converged on a similar set of foundational principles: First, they maintain a deep commitment to flavor above all else. Second, they possess a desire to make transparent the sources of flavor, in contrast to many manufacturers whose ingredients are secret or veiled. And finally, they are interested in supporting and sustaining the farmers, foragers and ecosystems whose products they distill. Head to the link in our profile for more from @tjdnewyork on the distillers making spirits that defy traditional categorization. #drinkpunch 📷⁠

node.text: Northern California was the source of inspiration for @pamwiz's Cold in the Shadows, where the drink's key ingredients tie back to the region—the IPA from @andersonvalleybrewing and @stgeorgespirits raspberry liqueur from Alameda. Add in honey syrup and lime juice and the result is a drink that tastes just like a bitter shandy. But you don't have to be in California to enjoy it, check out the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Say hello to an instant summer classic by way of Spain. The Tinto Tónico is inspired by the country's obsession with G&Ts and their summer drink Tinto de Verano, head to the link in our profile for the simple and refreshing recipe. #drinkpunch 📷: @alexabendak

node.text: “The future of cocktails seems to be leaning more and more toward savory items,” says @caermaiko, our 2021 Bartender in Residence, who builds her Tendril Loving Care, a Collins-style drink, around a snap pea shrub made with vinegar and mint. She then mixes it with lime juice, gin and an olive oil-washed blanco tequila and finishes it off with soda water. You can find the recipe at the link in our profile. #bartenderinresidence #drinkpunch 📷: @jessattie

node.text: The official drink of the Caribbean’s French-speaking islands (notably, Martinique), the Ti’ Punch is a simple combo of grassy, funky agricole rum made from fresh-pressed sugar cane, cane sugar and a lime peel. But similar to the Old-Fashioned, everyone seems to have their own riff.  The drink has become not a fixed recipe, but a format that can bend to each drinker’s preference—and today, that preference has gone far beyond the choice of how to cut one’s lime coin. Head to the link in our profile for five variations that prove the Ti Punch has got moves. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Last week we tasted through more than 40 wines, from pét-nat to piquette, to come up with a list of at least five wines we’d be happy to drink any day of the week. We had a tough time keeping it to 10. Coinciding with the rise of natural wine, the category has exploded over the past few years. So, without any further ado, head to the link in our profile for the complex, yet crushable cans that deserve a spot in your cooler this summer. Big thanks to our panel of tasters: @zacharysussman, @taliabaiocchi, @migueld1, @zwanng and Eliza Christen. #drinkpunch

node.text: It looks like any other Martini. But at @thunderboltla, the classically dry cocktail is transformed into a complex umami bomb with one sleeper ingredient: tomato water. The Liquid Picnic—a mixture of gin, vermouth, salt, pepper and clarified tomato water—"reads like a salad, drinks like a Martini.” The tomato water adds texture and subtle savory notes to the drink while working double-time as the drink’s only form of dilution. @mfcapoferri  uses a centrifuge for clarification at the Los Angeles bar, but we've got a home-friendly variation via the link in our profile. 📷: @lizzieamunro
